#############################################################################

Dependencies

  Python 2.7
  py2exe              # to build windows exe
  py2app              # to build mac app
  git                 # to work with files
  computer
    no server         # an existing server disrupts our temp server
    admin access      # to setup a server we need admin access


#############################################################################

Run Subi

  For mac
  
    1. Build subi (instructions below)

    2. Kill any exisiting webservers (may be unecessary)
       ps -a                      # find the process id of the webserver
       e.g. sudo kill -9 24234    # if the process id was 24234

    3. Change into subi directory
       e.g. cd subi

    4. Launch subi server
       sudo dist/Subi.app/Contents/MacOS/Subi

    5. Visit subi webpage
       http://localhost/subi

  For Windows

    1. Build subi (instructions below)

    2. Launch subi server
       subi/dist/subi.exe

    3. Visit subi webpage
       http://localhost/subi


#############################################################################

Build subi

  To build a mac or windows application

    1. Start in subi directory
       e.g. cd subi/

    2. Remove previous build lines
       rm -rf build/ dist/

    3. Build the app

       (for mac)
       python setup.py py2app     # Add -A to use source files

       (for windows)
       python setup.py py2exe     # Add -A to use source files


  Edit build setup

    setup.py code was borrowed from 
    http://svn.pythonmac.org/py2app/py2app/trunk/doc/index.html#self-bootstrapping
    It is made to setup both windows and mac.
    There are many options that can be changed.
    Just be sure to avoid the option ARGV which kills mac


